            <div class="align-items-center content">
                <h1 class="text-light text-center">Learn More How To Use Our Platform!!!</h1>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div id="containerMain" class="container">
    <div class="row justify-content-center align-items-center">
            <h2 class="tex-center display-2 mb-5">Video Guide</h2>
            <br>
        <div class="col-md-8 mb-5">
            <div class="embed-responsive embed-responsive-16by9">
                <iframe class="embed-responsive-item" src="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1i-9S80P1gpj3ghlKL5f9hF5Nnhxu1efo/view?usp=sharing"></iframe>
            </div>
        </div>
        <br>
        <h2 class="display-2 mt-4 mx-auto">Command List</h2>
    </div>
    <table class="table table-striped font-weight-light">
        <thead class="thead-dark text-center">
            <tr>
                <th scope="col"><strong>#</strong></th>
                <th scope="col"><strong>Command</strong></th>
                <th scope="col"><strong>Details</strong></th>
              </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr>
                <th scope="row">1</th>
                <th><strong>/commandlist</strong></th>
                <th>
                    This is a command to see all the available commands to use the bot.
                    <br>
                    <strong>How to use :</strong> type "/commandlist" and hit send.
                </th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <th scope="row">2</th>
                <th><strong>/help</strong></th>
                <th>
                    This is a command that give you the guide on how to use the Telegram Bot. 
                    <br>
                    <strong>How to use :</strong> type "/help" and hit send.
                </th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <th scope="row">3</th>
                <th><strong>/join</strong></th>
                <th>
                    This is a command to join the group collate order. After inputting this to the bot, and <strong>invite link</strong> 
                    will be given. The group number will be given in the personal <strong>notification</strong> by the bot. 
                    <br>
                    <strong>How to use :</strong> type "/join(space)(random number generated by the bot)" and hit send.
                </th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <th scope="row">4</th>
                <th><strong>/logout</strong></th>
                <th>
                    This is a command to logout from your current account.
                    <br>
                    <strong>How to use :</strong> type "/logout" and hit send.
                </th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <th scope="row">5</th>
                <th><strong>/orderfrom</strong></th>
                <th>
                    This is a command to set which restaurant you are ordering from. To check the name of the restaurant, you can use other 
                    command such as <strong>/categorylist</strong>, <strong>/restaurantlist</strong>, and <strong>/searchrestaurant</strong>. 
                    <br>
                    <strong>How to use :</strong> type "/orderfrom(space)(the name of the restaurant)" , "/orderfrom KOI" for 
                    example, and hit send.
                </th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <th scope="row">6</th>
                <th><strong>/orderto</strong></th>
                <th>
                    This is a command to set the place you want the food to be delivered. You just need to type in your address and 
                    the <strong>GoogleMap API</strong> will set the place for you. 
                    <br>
                    <strong>How to use :</strong> type "/orderto(space)(your address)" , "/orderto Ridge View Residential College" for 
                    example, and hit send.
                </th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <th scope="row">7</th>
                <th><strong>/invitelink</strong></th>
                <th>
                    This is a command to set you collate group's invite link to the group. You just need to open your group's detail 
                    and copy the invitation link and then paste it to the command.
                    <br>
                    <strong>How to use :</strong> type "/invitelink(space)(paste the invite link here)" and hit send.
                </th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <th scope="row">8</th>
                <th><strong>/ordertime</strong></th>
                <th>
                    This is a command to set your recommended waiting time (in minutes) for others to order. Our Telegram bot will then put this 
                    in the <strong>notification</strong> for other users to see. 
                    <br>
                    <strong>How to use :</strong> type "/ordertime(space)(your preferred order waiting time in minutes)", 
                    "/ordertime 15" for example, and hit send.
                </th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <th scope="row">9</th>
                <th><strong>/paymenttime</strong></th>
                <th>
                    This is a command to set your recommended waiting time (in minutes) for others to pay you (if you created the 
                    group). Our Telegram bot will then put this in the <strong>notification</strong> for other users to see. 
                    <br>
                    <strong>How to use :</strong> type "/paymenttime(space)(your preferred payment time limit in minutes)", 
                    "/paymenttime 15" for example, and hit send.
                </th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <th scope="row">10</th>
                <th><strong>/finalizeorder</strong></th>
                <th>
                    This is a command to set and finalize the order and the bot will accept this comment and notify everyone near 
                    the inputted location. In order to use this, you need to use <strong>/orderfrom</strong>, <strong>/orderto</strong>, 
                    <strong>/invitelink</strong>, <strong>/ordertime</strong>, and <strong>/paymenttime</strong> and you can not use 
                    other command beside these 5.
                    <br>
                    <strong>How to use :</strong> type "/finalizeorder" and hit send.
                </th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <th scope="row">11</th>
                <th><strong>/reset</strong></th>
                <th>
                    This is a command to reset all your orders details. You can only use this command before using <strong>/finalizeorder</strong> 
                    command. After resetting the detail, you need to fill in <strong>/orderfrom</strong>, <strong>/orderto</strong>, 
                    <strong>/invitelink</strong>, <strong>/ordertime</strong>, and <strong>/paymenttime</strong> again. 
                    <br>
                    <strong>How to use :</strong> type "/reset" and hit send.
                </th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <th scope="row">12</th>
                <th><strong>/orderstatus</strong></th>
                <th>
                    This is a command to view the status of your current order, including the waiting time for both ordering and payment, 
                    added order/food menu, which restaurant you are ordering from, etc. 
                    <br>
                    <strong>How to use :</strong> type "/orderstatus" and hit send.
                </th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <th scope="row">13</th>
                <th><strong>/categorylist</strong></th>
                <th>
                    This is a command to see what food or restaurant categories are available in our database. The bot will then send 
                    all the available categories in the group. <strong>This command can be used before and after finalize order</strong>
                    <br>
                    <strong>How to use :</strong> type "/categorylist" and hit send.
                </th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <th scope="row">14</th>
                <th><strong>/restaurantlist</strong></th>
                <th>
                    This is a command to see all the restaurants inside a certain category. You need to type in the category after this 
                    command and our bot will send you all available restaurant inside that category. <strong>This command can be used before and after finalize order</strong>
                    <br>
                    <strong>How to use :</strong> type "/restaurantlist(space)(the category)", 
                    "/restaurantlist Korean" for example, and hit send.
                </th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <th scope="row">15</th>
                <th><strong>/menu</strong></th>
                <th>
                    This is a command to see all the menus of a certain restaurant. You need to type in the name of the restaurant after this 
                    command and our bot will send you the menu of that restaurant. <strong>This command can be used before and after finalize order</strong>
                    <br>
                    <strong>How to use :</strong> type "/menu(space)(name of the restaurant)", 
                    "/menu KOI" for example, and hit send.
                </th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <th scope="row">16</th>
                <th><strong>/searchrestaurant</strong></th>
                <th>
                    This is a command to search an available restaurant with the help of a keyword.
                    <br>
                    <strong>How to use :</strong> type "/searchrestaurant(space)(the keyword", 
                    "/searchrestaurant Burger" for example, and hit send.
                </th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <th scope="row">17</th>
                <th><strong>/foodinfo</strong></th>
                <th>
                    This is a command to search an available restaurant with the help of a keyword.
                    <br>
                    <strong>How to use :</strong> type "/searchrestaurant(space)(the keyword)", 
                    "/searchrestaurant Burger" for example, and hit send.
                </th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <th scope="row">18</th>
                <th><strong>/add</strong></th>
                <th>
                    This is a command to add food(s) to the collated order.
                    <br>
                    <strong>How to use :</strong> type "/add(space)(name of the food)", "/add Korean Gimbap" for example, and hit send. 
                    You can also add "--" to add description to your food ("/add Korean Gimbap -- extra sauce").
                </th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <th scope="row">19</th>
                <th><strong>/remove</strong></th>
                <th>
                    This is a command to remove a food from the collated order. You can only remove what you have ordered before.
                    <br>
                    <strong>How to use :</strong> type "/remove(space)(the name of the food)", 
                    "/remove Kimchi Stew" for example, and hit send.
                </th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <th scope="row">20</th>
                <th><strong>/removeall</strong></th>
                <th>
                    This is a command to remove all the food you have ordered from the collated order. In case you change your mind 
                    and want to change your order, you can use this command.
                    <br>
                    <strong>How to use :</strong> type "/removeall" and hit send.
                </th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <th scope="row">21</th>
                <th><strong>/deliverycost</strong></th>
                <th>
                    This is a command to input the delivery fee of the order. The person who created the group have to do this command 
                    after the order time limit ended. The bot will then take in the value and divide the price based on how many people 
                    are in the group.
                    <br>
                    <strong>How to use :</strong> type "/deliverycost(space)(the price)", 
                    "/deliverycost 5.10" for example, and hit send.
                </th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <th scope="row">22</th>
                <th><strong>/verifyuser</strong></th>
                <th>
                    This is a command to verify a user when a user in the group have paid the one who created the group for the order.
                    <br>
                    <strong>How to use :</strong> type "/verifyuser(space)(the username)", 
                    "/verifyuser @john_legend" for example, and hit send.
                </th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <th scope="row">23</th>
                <th><strong>/unverifyuser</strong></th>
                <th>
                    This is a command to unverify a user if you accidentaly typo and verify the wrong user.
                    <br>
                    <strong>How to use :</strong> type "/unverifyuser(space)(the username)", 
                    "/unverifyuser @taylor_swift" for example, and hit send.
                </th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <th scope="row">24</th>
                <th><strong>/history</strong></th>
                <th>
                    This is a command to see all you previous orders.
                    <br>
                    <strong>How to use :</strong> type "/history" and hit send.
                </th>
            </tr>
        </tbody>

    </table>
</div>
